title: For Trade:  Like New Barrnett Vengeance Crossbow
postcontent:
Barnett Vengeance
 Just in time for bow season!!!


Personifying a steely resolve and determination, the new Barnett Vengeance crossbow is aptly named. The Barnett Vengeance represents a quantum leap in crossbow evolution. It is the first crossbow to combine a lightweight CarbonLite Riser with reverse draw technology. As a result, the Vengeance exhibits significantly less vibration and noise than a traditional draw crossbow without sacrificing speed or accuracy.

In this radical new reverse draw configuration, the limb pockets are moved closer to the trigger assembly and the limbs face forward on the bow, thus shifting the center of gravity closer to the shooter’s body. This drastically reduces the weight at the front of the crossbow, which is essential for a well-balanced shot.

In addition, the Vengeance features a CarbonLite Riser assembly, which further reduces the weight without compromising strength or accuracy. The most technically advanced riser ever created for a crossbow, the CarbonLite Riser removes approximately 43 percent of weight from the front end, which dramatically shifts the balance point to the shoulder. The combination of the reverse draw design with the CarbonLite Riser allows the Vengeance to provide the steadiest and most accurate shot possible.

Like all other Barnett Crossbows, the Vengeance is proudly made in the USA.

Specs:

Speed: 365 fps.
Draw Weight: 140 pounds.
Power Stroke: 18 inches.
From its inception, over a half century ago, Barnett Crossbows has led the industry with pioneering innovations and patents to become the world’s number one manufacturer of crossbows. Barnett’s engineers have created its latest range of crossbows based on the changing needs and desires of today’s hunters. Lightweight, adjustable and powerful, Barnett has brought crossbow technology to the height it stands at today. Barnett is committed to delivering high quality performance products with unparalleled service and value for all that use the Barnett Range. Built for maximum speed, efficiency and Built for the Hunt!

Stock has a W and a Ordnance bomb mark in the slingwell.

Has RRA and RIA/EB rebuild marks on left side.

There is a non-serifed 'P' in a circle on the wrist. Directly above that is a non-serifed 'P' in a box.

Every single carbine you find in "original" condition is rebuilt/restored, unless it was sold by the old DCM and there are papers to prove it, and many of those were in fact rebuilt.There have been some appear on CMP auction from what I understand as well. However, the majority of "correct" carbines use mix-matched parts, or reproduction parts that are junk.
 The only other way an original carbine exists is for a GI from years ago to have stolen it from the government. There were no "bringbacks" of US weapons. If he brought it home, he stole it, period. Every other one was rebuilt, most of them several times over, and constantly upgraded by unit and post level armorers. Yes, it has a flat bolt and a four handguard, as most of the two rivet ones would break, hence the upgrade to the four rivet.

No mags for sale. Stay away from most USGI 30 rounders, as the springs are worn and they do not feed. Test any and all you plan to use, and you will find the failure rate on those is high. Numrich/Sarco used to have rebuild kits for them and then they work fine if the bodies are in good repair.

Other than the IP this is the rarest of the carbines.

Not sure who flagged this when I posted it before, but I would appreciate it if you would not take this down as it is not a scam. If you do not like the price, dont buy it. Have the courtesy of emailing me and asking questions rather than identifying this for flagging. This is a real M1 Carbine, for sale by a real person.
Thank you.

title: For Sale:  Marine Valtro PM5 18" 2 Mags, 3 Stocks, Shroud
postcontent:
Unusual Valtro PM5 twelve gauge shotgun, manufactured for Valtro under contract by Benelli. The PM5 is an uncommon design because it uses a detachable seven round box magazine, and was available with either a Monte Carlo style fixed stock, a fixed pistol grip stock, or a skeleton wire frame stock that doubles as a carry handle when folded. The rear folding stock assembly can be easily removed by extracting a single pin resulting in a pistol grip only configuration. The Valtro is reported to be one of the most reliable and fastest cycling pump shotguns available, and the detachable box magazine is an excellent feature; resulting in faster full reload times and better balance since the ammo load is directly under the receiver instead of forward under the barrel.

This is the Marine rated grey finish version, NOT the standard black matte anodized that is much more common.

Basic features include:

18.5” barrel (later models had 20” with available porting)

3” chamber (will fit 2 3/4 and 3 inch shells)

Threaded for choke tubes (cylinder choke included, uses Benelli tubes)

Alloy receiver with Marine rated finish

7 round detachable box magazine (+1 in chamber)

This early version weapon is in very good cosmetic condition except for a few scuffs around the magazine well and some rub marks on the upper left receiver, likely from a sling swivel (some “touch-up” has been applied at some point). It is not a “safe queen” but it is not a “range rat” either and is offered in AS-IS but in fully functional condition. The set includes everything pictured, a Valtro PM5 shotgun, the factory fixed pistol grip stock, the factory folding pistol grip stock, and TWO functional factory seven round magazines.

In addition to the extra magazine, this weapon also comes with a vented steel barrel shroud installed as well as a specially customized  M4 style collapsible stock and pistol grip assembly unavailable anywhere else. The adapter is composite, the mount is anodized aluminum (NOT plastic), the buffer tube is five position adjustable, includes a basic A2 grip and stock with removable buffer pad. This assembly will allow the installation of ANY available M16/AR-15 grip or stock on the market!

$1000 or best offer, please feel free to ask questions, and thank you for your interest.

REDACTED
